pageContext.claim: “The European Union has been very restrictive. They don't take a lot -- not only farm products; medical products. So many products they don't take. And yet, we take theirs. And when they do take our product, they charge us massive tax -- massive. A tariff -- massive. And we take theirs, same product, we charge them almost nothing.”
pageContext.analysis: The European Union is the U.S.'s biggest trading partner, with total trade of more than $700 billion.
